Problem Statement 1
Problem statement

Profit margins are a challenging world. It is easy to get lost trying to figure out profit margin ratios, operating profit margins, net versus growth, and more. It can be tricky to overcome the information overload and actually learn how to increase profit for your business.
Gross margin helps a company figure out how much money it keeps after incurring the costs related to making the product it sells and/or the service it provides. Higher margins can indicate whether a company is running a profitable operation and if sales are good. As a general rule of thumb, a 10%net profit margin is deemed average, while a 20% margin is deemed high and 5% low.
